<p>
  We offer educational sessions tailored to different roles — designers, developers, content authors, and managers. Sessions range from accessibility fundamentals to hands-on technical workshops.
</p>

<h2>Session formats</h2>
<ul class="list-disc mb-300">
  <li class="mb-75"><strong>Introductory workshops</strong> — an overview of digital accessibility, WCAG, and applicable Government of Canada requirements</li>
  <li class="mb-75"><strong>Role-specific sessions</strong> — targeted guidance for designers, developers, or content authors</li>
  <li><strong>One-on-one coaching</strong> — hands-on support for teams working through remediation or learning new skills</li>
</ul>

<h2>Coaching</h2>
<p>
  Coaching sessions are available for teams actively remediating accessibility issues or embedding accessibility into their processes for the first time. Coaching is practical and grounded in your actual product and workflow.
</p>

<h2>Request training or coaching</h2>
<p>
  Contact us at <a href="mailto:aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca">aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca</a> to discuss your team's needs. Include the number of participants, their roles, and any specific topics you want us to cover.
</p>

